  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 trigger)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD model targets the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry and estimates absolute hemolysis index values. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across operating flow rates from 3 to 7 L/min at 2500–3500 RPM. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. The assessment team concluded that, for the specific operating envelope studied, the model achieves sufficient credibility for the intended comparative-design use. No structured Context of Use object is attached to this package; the intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative description.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-prediction-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset-2019",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-benchmark-dataset-2021"
  ],
