  "signature": "ed25519:9a2b4c6d8e1f3a5b7c9d2e4f6a8b1c3d5e7f9a2b4c6d8e1f3a5b7c9d2e4f6a8b",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented regression test suite covering all relevant physics modules; independent code review completed.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM v8) is version-controlled and a regression suite exists, but the suite does not cover the hemolysis damage integral module. Independent code review was not performed. Achieved level falls one gradation below required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equations including turbulence closure; order-of-accuracy confirmed.",
      "rationale": "MMS was applied to the Navier-Stokes and continuity equations confirming second-order spatial accuracy. The k-omega SST turbulence model and the power-law hemolysis scalar transport equation were not subjected to MMS; this gap reduces the achieved level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes with GCI below 2% for all QoIs; mesh sensitivity documented for boundary layer resolution in blade tip clearance.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted (4 M, 12 M, 28 M cells). GCI for the global hemolysis index was 8.3%, exceeding the 2% threshold. Tip-clearance boundary-layer resolution was insufficient on the coarse and medium meshes. Achieved level is 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) match simulation boundary conditions within stated uncertainty bands; traceability to NIST standards documented.",
      "rationale": "Flow rate and rotational speed match within 1.5% and 0.8% respectively. Fluid temperature was controlled to ±0.5°C. Hematocrit was fixed at 35% in simulation but ranged 33–37% in experiments. NIST traceability documented for flow and pressure sensors but not for the hemolysis spectrophotometer."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (e.g., E_rms) computed with uncertainty propagation for all primary QoIs; validation domain covers full clinical operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Normalized RMS error for hemolysis index is 18.4% across the five tested operating points, exceeding acceptable thresholds. Validation was performed at 5 L/min and 3500 RPM only; the full 3–7 L/min envelope was not covered. Uncertainty propagation was performed via Monte Carlo but intervals overlap experimental data at only 3 of 5 points."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted QoIs (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) directly correspond to the clinical decision metric; mapping between model output and device risk criterion is formally documented.",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis index is directly relevant to device risk. However, the formal mapping from model-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) to the regulatory threshold (NIH < 0.1 g/100 L) is described only qualitatively. Shear stress distribution was not extracted as a separate QoI."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments replicate the clinical COU geometry, fluid properties, and operating regime; any differences are bounded and their impact on extrapolation uncertainty is quantified.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry, which is a simplified surrogate for actual VAD designs. Fluid was bovine blood rather than human blood. The operating regime partially overlaps the clinical envelope. Extrapolation uncertainty from surrogate geometry to clinical device was not formally quantified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residual below 1e-6 for all equations; round-off error analysis performed; solver settings documented and justified.",
      "rationale": "Iterative residuals were monitored and reached 1e-4 for momentum and 1e-5 for continuity, not meeting the 1e-6 target. Round-off error analysis was not performed. This factor was flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5 and is recorded as not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented user qualification, simulation execution checklist, and independent peer review of simulation setup by a second qualified analyst.",
      "rationale": "No formal user qualification record exists. A simulation execution checklist was drafted but not formally approved. Independent peer review of the simulation setup was not conducted. This factor represents a significant epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics model selection (turbulence closure, hemolysis damage model) justified against experimental evidence; alternative model forms evaluated; model-form uncertainty quantified.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected based on prior literature but no systematic comparison against k-epsilon or LES was performed for this geometry. The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model was used without evaluation of the Zhang or Taskin alternatives. Model-form uncertainty was not quantified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterized with probability distributions; sensitivity analysis identifies dominant inputs; input uncertainty propagated through Monte Carlo with at least 1000 samples.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 500 samples, below the 1000-sample threshold. Blood viscosity and density were assigned uniform distributions without supporting experimental characterization data. The hemolysis model exponents (C, alpha, beta) were treated as fixed constants rather than uncertain parameters, which is a significant omission at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Biological variability in blood samples characterized; minimum sample size determined by power analysis; donor demographics and anticoagulation protocols documented.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis data were collected from a single batch of bovine blood from one supplier. No power analysis was performed to determine minimum sample size. Donor information and anticoagulation protocols were not documented in the test report. This factor is an unresolved epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters demonstrated to match experimental conditions through formal equivalency analysis; any deviations bounded and impact assessed.",
      "rationale": "No formal equivalency analysis was performed between simulation boundary conditions and experimental test conditions. The inlet velocity profile was assumed fully developed whereas the experimental rig used a short inlet section. This structural mismatch was not bounded or assessed for impact on QoI predictions."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-biofluidics-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team accepted this model for comparative design screening use within the studied operating envelope (5 L/min, 3500 RPM), acknowledging that six credibility factors remain as epistemic gaps and that absolute hemolysis prediction accuracy does not meet MRL 5 thresholds for regulatory submission. Acceptance is conditional on the model being used only for relative ranking of design variants and not for standalone regulatory claims. The team noted that the absence of a structured Context of Use object in this package means the intended-use scope is defined solely by this narrative record, which the team considered sufficient for internal research purposes.",
